description.p:
More completely, a conveyor and for example web conveyor assembly is provided comprising:
a first conveyor/ web section;
a first linkage assembly in accordance with the above;
a second conveyor/ web section;
a second linkage assembly in accordance with the above.

More completely, an assembled conveyor and for example web conveyor is provided comprising:
a first conveyor/ web section;
a first linkage assembly in accordance with the above;
a second conveyor/ web section;
a second linkage assembly in accordance with the above;
wherein a conveyor engagement portion of the first linkage assembly is mounted to an end of the first conveyor/ web section in fixed rigid relationship;
a conveyor engagement portion of the second linkage assembly is mounted to an end of the second conveyor/ web section in fixed rigid relationship;
the respective linkage formations of the first and second linkage assemblies are mounted together in rigid fixed relationship.

More completely, a method for the articulated connection of two sections of an endless conveyor and for example of a web for use in an endless web conveyor is provided comprising:
providing a first conveyor section and a first linkage assembly in accordance with the above;
connecting the same;
providing a second conveyor section and a second linkage assembly in accordance with the above;
connecting the same;
thereafter mounting together the respective linkage formations of the first and second linkage assemblies in rigid fixed relationship.

The invention will now be described by way of example only with reference to figures 1 and 2 of the accompanying drawings in which:
Figure 1 is a cross section through a web belt of a web conveyor linked in accordance with a linkage of an embodiment of the invention;
Figure 2 is a plan view of the linkage system illustrated in figure 1.

claim.claim-text:
A conveyor assembly comprising at least:
a first web section;
a first linkage assembly (L1) in accordance with any preceding claim;
a second web section;
a second linkage assembly (L2) in accordance with any preceding claim.

An assembled conveyor comprising at least:
a first web section;
a first linkage assembly (L1) in accordance with any preceding claim;
a second web section;
a second linkage assembly (L2) in accordance with any preceding claim;
wherein a conveyor engagement portion (8) of the first linkage assembly (L1) is mounted to an end of the first web section in fixed rigid relationship;
a conveyor engagement portion (8) of the second linkage (L2) assembly is mounted to an end of the second web section in fixed rigid relationship; and
the respective linkage formations (11a, 11b) of the first and second linkage assemblies (L1, L2) are mounted together in rigid fixed relationship.

A method for the articulated connection of two sections of an endless conveyor and for example of a web for use in an endless web conveyor is provided comprising:
providing a first conveyor section and a first linkage assembly in accordance with any one of claims 1 to 14;
connecting the same;
providing a second conveyor section and a second linkage assembly in accordance with any one of claims 1 to 14;
connecting the same;
thereafter mounting together the respective linkage formations of the first and second linkage assemblies in rigid fixed relationship.
